ristian ethics. It reveals that, alongside the confessional churches, it is also the social forms of marriage, family, and friendship, bourgeois society, the state, and the cosmopolitan connection between all humans that, each in itself and collectively, constitute the cultural effectiveness of Christianity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aChristian ethics. 0aChristian sociology. 0aSocial sciencesxPhilosophy. 4aKirche. 4aSchleiermacher, Friedrich. 4aTheorie des Christentums. 4achristliche Sittenlehre. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh  aChristian ethics.  aSchleiermacher, Friedrich.  achurch.  atheory of Christianity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831110270360 cprintz978311102538440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311102645940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111026459423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111026459/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK